law.text:
The Energy and Environment Cabinet shall enforce the rules and regulations adopted by the secretary of the Energy and Environment Cabinet for the regulation and control of the matters set out below and shall formulate, promote, establish and execute policies, plans and programs relating to natural resources and environmental protection, including but not limited to the following matters:
The proper disposal of waste;
The purification of water for public and semipublic use;
The proper construction and operation of public water distribution systems and water treatment systems in public water purification plants and swimming pools;
The review, approval or disapproval of plans for construction, modification or extension of water purification and distribution systems and water treatment systems in swimming pools; and
The certification of water and sewage plant operators.
